OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FIn normal circumstances, Keir
OL,7,FStarmer's appointment of Gordon Brown
OL,8,Fas his special envoy on global finance
OL,9,Fand Harriet Harman as his adviser on
OL,10,Fwomen and girls would be seen by
OL,11,FLabour MPs as sensible.
OL,13,FTapping the wisdom of the party's
OL,14,Felders to solve important problems
OL,15,Fwould be viewed as competent if dull
OL,16,Ftechnocratic government.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FHowever, these are not normal
OL,7,Fcircumstances for the Prime Minister.
OL,8,FHis MPs see him as responsible for
OL,9,Fyesterday's electoral catastrophe. He
OL,10,Findeed has insisted he does take full
OL,11,Fresponsibility.
OL,13,FAnd that is why the appointments are
OL,14,Fin fact incendiary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FBecause they are seen as - at best -
OL,7,Firrelevant to the crisis faced by the
OL,8,Fgovernment, and for many MPs and
OL,9,Fministers they are provocative, an
OL,10,Finsult, a manifestation - in the words
OL,11,Fof one minister - "that he simply
OL,12,Fdoesn't get it."
OL,14,FThis is what one senior and
OL,15,Finfluential member of the government
OL,16,Ftold me:
OL,26,@sD@SOUtD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,F"The Harriet and Gordon thing and his
OL,7,FGuardian article (in which he said the
OL,8,Fgovernment should neither move left or
OL,9,Fright) has annoyed Labour MPs even
OL,10,Fmore. It's tone deaf. I think people
OL,11,Fgive him until Monday to actually show
OL,12,Fhe gets it or he's done."
OL,14,FTo be clear, this minister would often
OL,15,Ftry to defend the PM. Not any more.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@RpmqD@FpntD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FAnd that's not altogether surprising,
OL,7,Fgiven that few Reform voters are
OL,8,Flikely to say "I was thinking of
OL,9,Fvoting for Nigel Farage but I've
OL,10,Fchanged my mind now that Keir has
OL,11,Ftapped Gordon to create an
OL,12,Finternational off-balance-sheet
OL,13,Ffinance facility for defence spending."
OL,15,FAnother minister told me that the
OL,16,Fpreference of MPs and Labour's members
OL,17,Fwould be for Starmer to stay and turn
OL,18,Faround the performance of the
OL,19,Fgovernment, but they were increasingly
OL,20,Fdoubtful he was capable of doing this.
OL,26,@pD@OOUuD@gO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FThus minister's mood, and that of his
OL,7,Fcolleagues, he said, "was increasingly
OL,8,Fof despair".
OL,10,FPerhaps the biggest problem was that
OL,11,FStarmer "is seemingly unable to give a
OL,12,Fclear coherent sense of direction for
OL,13,Fthe country."
OL,15,F"Voters will forgive you many of your
OL,16,Fmistakes if you can tell them where
OL,17,Fyou want to take them. But he has been
OL,18,Fincapable of doing that, and none of
OL,19,Fus know whether he ever can."
OL,26,@oD@VOUpD@KO]sD@IOUuD@MO]wD@AOU{D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FEven those members of the Cabinet who
OL,7,Fare genuine loyalists talk about him
OL,8,Fon the basis of hypothesis and
OL,9,Fguesswork.
OL,11,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,12,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,13,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,14,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,16,FNone of them seem to actually know
OL,17,Fwhat makes him tick or what he wants
OL,18,F(one told me he was planning to set
OL,19,Fout his own policies more publicly in
OL,20,Fthe hope that perhaps the PM would
OL,21,Fadopt them).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FIn that sense, Starmer seems more
OL,7,Fisolated than any prime minister I've
OL,8,Fever known.
OL,10,FA very big test for him comes on
OL,11,FMonday, when he is expected to give a
OL,12,Fspeech that will be billed as his
OL,13,Fagenda for the rest of the parliament,
OL,14,Fbut is in practice a plea to his MPs
OL,15,Fto give him a last chance.
OL,17,FI asked a minister what MPs would need
OL,18,Fto hear to be clear that he does
OL,19,Funderstand their concerns, that he
OL,20,F"gets it".
OL,26,@|D@AOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778454187
OL,3,CStarmer has 'till Monday' to save
OL,4,Chimself
OL,6,FThis was the reply. "I mean god knows
OL,7,Fbecause I dont think he does. It's not
OL,8,Fanything anyone else can tell him it
OL,9,Fhas to come from him."
OL,11,FAnd that, in a nutshell, is why
OL,12,FStarmer is in so much trouble.
OL,14,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,15,Four political experts are across all
OL,16,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,17,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,26,@nD@UOUqD@VO]
